2733
2734class bigint {
2735 private:
2736 // A bigint is stored as an array of bigits (big digits), with bigit at index
2737 // 0 being the least significant one.
2738 using bigit = uint32_t;
2739 using double_bigit = uint64_t;
2740 enum { bigits_capacity = 32 };
2741 basic_memory_buffer<bigit, bigits_capacity> bigits_;
2742 int exp_;
2743
2744 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto operator[](int index) const -> bigit {
2745 return bigits_[to_unsigned(index)];
2746 }
2747 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto operator[](int index) -> bigit& {
2748 return bigits_[to_unsigned(index)];
2749 }
2750
2751 static constexpr const int bigit_bits = num_bits<bigit>();
2752
2753 friend struct formatter<bigint>;
2754
2755 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void subtract_bigits(int index, bigit other, bigit& borrow) {
2756 auto result = static_cast<double_bigit>((*this)[index]) - other - borrow;
2757 (*this)[index] = static_cast<bigit>(result);
2758 borrow = static_cast<bigit>(result >> (bigit_bits * 2 - 1));
2759 }
2760
2761 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void remove_leading_zeros() {
2762 int num_bigits = static_cast<int>(bigits_.size()) - 1;
2763 while (num_bigits > 0 && (*this)[num_bigits] == 0) --num_bigits;
2764 bigits_.resize(to_unsigned(num_bigits + 1));
2765 }
2766
2767 // Computes *this -= other assuming aligned bigints and *this >= other.
2768 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void subtract_aligned(const bigint& other) {
2769 FMT_ASSERT(other.exp_ >= exp_, "unaligned bigints");
2770 FMT_ASSERT(compare(*this, other) >= 0, "");
2771 bigit borrow = 0;
2772 int i = other.exp_ - exp_;
2773 for (size_t j = 0, n = other.bigits_.size(); j != n; ++i, ++j)
2774 subtract_bigits(i, other.bigits_[j], borrow);
2775 while (borrow > 0) subtract_bigits(i, 0, borrow);
2776 remove_leading_zeros();
2777 }
2778
2779 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void multiply(uint32_t value) {
2780 const double_bigit wide_value = value;
2781 bigit carry = 0;
2782 for (size_t i = 0, n = bigits_.size(); i < n; ++i) {
2783 double_bigit result = bigits_[i] * wide_value + carry;
2784 bigits_[i] = static_cast<bigit>(result);
2785 carry = static_cast<bigit>(result >> bigit_bits);
2786 }
2787 if (carry != 0) bigits_.push_back(carry);
2788 }
2789
2790 template <typename UInt, FMT_ENABLE_IF(std::is_same<UInt, uint64_t>::value ||
2791 std::is_same<UInt, uint128_t>::value)>
2792 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void multiply(UInt value) {
2793 using half_uint =
2794 conditional_t<std::is_same<UInt, uint128_t>::value, uint64_t, uint32_t>;
2795 const int shift = num_bits<half_uint>() - bigit_bits;
2796 const UInt lower = static_cast<half_uint>(value);
2797 const UInt upper = value >> num_bits<half_uint>();
2798 UInt carry = 0;
2799 for (size_t i = 0, n = bigits_.size(); i < n; ++i) {
2800 UInt result = lower * bigits_[i] + static_cast<bigit>(carry);
2801 carry = (upper * bigits_[i] << shift) + (result >> bigit_bits) +
2802 (carry >> bigit_bits);
2803 bigits_[i] = static_cast<bigit>(result);
2804 }
2805 while (carry != 0) {
2806 bigits_.push_back(static_cast<bigit>(carry));
2807 carry >>= bigit_bits;
2808 }
2809 }
2810
2811 template <typename UInt, FMT_ENABLE_IF(std::is_same<UInt, uint64_t>::value ||
2812 std::is_same<UInt, uint128_t>::value)>
2813 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void assign(UInt n) {
2814 size_t num_bigits = 0;
2815 do {
2816 bigits_[num_bigits++] = static_cast<bigit>(n);
2817 n >>= bigit_bits;
2818 } while (n != 0);
2819 bigits_.resize(num_bigits);
2820 exp_ = 0;
2821 }
2822
2823 public:
2824 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 bigint() : exp_(0) {}
2825 explicit bigint(uint64_t n) { assign(n); }
2826
2827 bigint(const bigint&) = delete;
2828 void operator=(const bigint&) = delete;
2829
2830 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void assign(const bigint& other) {
2831 auto size = other.bigits_.size();
2832 bigits_.resize(size);
2833 auto data = other.bigits_.data();
2834 copy<bigit>(data, data + size, bigits_.data());
2835 exp_ = other.exp_;
2836 }
2837
2838 template <typename Int> FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void operator=(Int n) {
2839 FMT_ASSERT(n > 0, "");
2840 assign(uint64_or_128_t<Int>(n));
2841 }
2842
2843 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto num_bigits() const -> int {
2844 return static_cast<int>(bigits_.size()) + exp_;
2845 }
2846
2847 FMT_NOINLINE FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto operator<<=(int shift) -> bigint& {
2848 FMT_ASSERT(shift >= 0, "");
2849 exp_ += shift / bigit_bits;
2850 shift %= bigit_bits;
2851 if (shift == 0) return *this;
2852 bigit carry = 0;
2853 for (size_t i = 0, n = bigits_.size(); i < n; ++i) {
2854 bigit c = bigits_[i] >> (bigit_bits - shift);
2855 bigits_[i] = (bigits_[i] << shift) + carry;
2856 carry = c;
2857 }
2858 if (carry != 0) bigits_.push_back(carry);
2859 return *this;
2860 }
2861
2862 template <typename Int>
2863 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto operator*=(Int value) -> bigint& {
2864 FMT_ASSERT(value > 0, "");
2865 multiply(uint32_or_64_or_128_t<Int>(value));
2866 return *this;
2867 }
2868
2869 friend FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto compare(const bigint& lhs, const bigint& rhs)
2870 -> int {
2871 int num_lhs_bigits = lhs.num_bigits(), num_rhs_bigits = rhs.num_bigits();
2872 if (num_lhs_bigits != num_rhs_bigits)
2873 return num_lhs_bigits > num_rhs_bigits ? 1 : -1;
2874 int i = static_cast<int>(lhs.bigits_.size()) - 1;
2875 int j = static_cast<int>(rhs.bigits_.size()) - 1;
2876 int end = i - j;
2877 if (end < 0) end = 0;
2878 for (; i >= end; --i, --j) {
2879 bigit lhs_bigit = lhs[i], rhs_bigit = rhs[j];
2880 if (lhs_bigit != rhs_bigit) return lhs_bigit > rhs_bigit ? 1 : -1;
2881 }
2882 if (i != j) return i > j ? 1 : -1;
2883 return 0;
2884 }
2885
2886 // Returns compare(lhs1 + lhs2, rhs).
2887 friend FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto add_compare(const bigint& lhs1,
2888 const bigint& lhs2, const bigint& rhs)
2889 -> int {
2890 auto minimum = [](int a, int b) { return a < b ? a : b; };
2891 auto maximum = [](int a, int b) { return a > b ? a : b; };
2892 int max_lhs_bigits = maximum(lhs1.num_bigits(), lhs2.num_bigits());
2893 int num_rhs_bigits = rhs.num_bigits();
2894 if (max_lhs_bigits + 1 < num_rhs_bigits) return -1;
2895 if (max_lhs_bigits > num_rhs_bigits) return 1;
2896 auto get_bigit = [](const bigint& n, int i) -> bigit {
2897 return i >= n.exp_ && i < n.num_bigits() ? n[i - n.exp_] : 0;
2898 };
2899 double_bigit borrow = 0;
2900 int min_exp = minimum(minimum(lhs1.exp_, lhs2.exp_), rhs.exp_);
2901 for (int i = num_rhs_bigits - 1; i >= min_exp; --i) {
2902 double_bigit sum =
2903 static_cast<double_bigit>(get_bigit(lhs1, i)) + get_bigit(lhs2, i);
2904 bigit rhs_bigit = get_bigit(rhs, i);
2905 if (sum > rhs_bigit + borrow) return 1;
2906 borrow = rhs_bigit + borrow - sum;
2907 if (borrow > 1) return -1;
2908 borrow <<= bigit_bits;
2909 }
2910 return borrow != 0 ? -1 : 0;
2911 }
2912
2913 // Assigns pow(10, exp) to this bigint.
2914 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void assign_pow10(int exp) {
2915 FMT_ASSERT(exp >= 0, "");
2916 if (exp == 0) return *this = 1;
2917 // Find the top bit.
2918 int bitmask = 1;
2919 while (exp >= bitmask) bitmask <<= 1;
2920 bitmask >>= 1;
2921 // pow(10, exp) = pow(5, exp) * pow(2, exp). First compute pow(5, exp) by
2922 // repeated squaring and multiplication.
2923 *this = 5;
2924 bitmask >>= 1;
2925 while (bitmask != 0) {
2926 square();
2927 if ((exp & bitmask) != 0) *this *= 5;
2928 bitmask >>= 1;
2929 }
2930 *this <<= exp; // Multiply by pow(2, exp) by shifting.
2931 }
2932
2933 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void square() {
2934 int num_bigits = static_cast<int>(bigits_.size());
2935 int num_result_bigits = 2 * num_bigits;
2936 basic_memory_buffer<bigit, bigits_capacity> n(std::move(bigits_));
2937 bigits_.resize(to_unsigned(num_result_bigits));
2938 auto sum = uint128_t();
2939 for (int bigit_index = 0; bigit_index < num_bigits; ++bigit_index) {
2940 // Compute bigit at position bigit_index of the result by adding
2941 // cross-product terms n[i] * n[j] such that i + j == bigit_index.
2942 for (int i = 0, j = bigit_index; j >= 0; ++i, --j) {
2943 // Most terms are multiplied twice which can be optimized in the future.
2944 sum += static_cast<double_bigit>(n[i]) * n[j];
2945 }
2946 (*this)[bigit_index] = static_cast<bigit>(sum);
2947 sum >>= num_bits<bigit>(); // Compute the carry.
2948 }
2949 // Do the same for the top half.
2950 for (int bigit_index = num_bigits; bigit_index < num_result_bigits;
2951 ++bigit_index) {
2952 for (int j = num_bigits - 1, i = bigit_index - j; i < num_bigits;)
2953 sum += static_cast<double_bigit>(n[i++]) * n[j--];
2954 (*this)[bigit_index] = static_cast<bigit>(sum);
2955 sum >>= num_bits<bigit>();
2956 }
2957 remove_leading_zeros();
2958 exp_ *= 2;
2959 }
2960
2961 // If this bigint has a bigger exponent than other, adds trailing zero to make
2962 // exponents equal. This simplifies some operations such as subtraction.
2963 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void align(const bigint& other) {
2964 int exp_difference = exp_ - other.exp_;
2965 if (exp_difference <= 0) return;
2966 int num_bigits = static_cast<int>(bigits_.size());
2967 bigits_.resize(to_unsigned(num_bigits + exp_difference));
2968 for (int i = num_bigits - 1, j = i + exp_difference; i >= 0; --i, --j)
2969 bigits_[j] = bigits_[i];
2970 memset(bigits_.data(), 0, to_unsigned(exp_difference) * sizeof(bigit));
2971 exp_ -= exp_difference;
2972 }
2973
2974 // Divides this bignum by divisor, assigning the remainder to this and
2975 // returning the quotient.
2976 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto divmod_assign(const bigint& divisor) -> int {
2977 FMT_ASSERT(this != &divisor, "");
2978 if (compare(*this, divisor) < 0) return 0;
2979 FMT_ASSERT(divisor.bigits_[divisor.bigits_.size() - 1u] != 0, "");
2980 align(divisor);
2981 int quotient = 0;
2982 do {
2983 subtract_aligned(divisor);
2984 ++quotient;
2985 } while (compare(*this, divisor) >= 0);
2986 return quotient;
2987 }
2988};

2990// format_dragon flags.
2991enum dragon {
2992 predecessor_closer = 1,
2993 fixup = 2, // Run fixup to correct exp10 which can be off by one.
2994 fixed = 4,

2997// Formats a floating-point number using a variation of the Fixed-Precision
2998// Positive Floating-Point Printout ((FPP)^2) algorithm by Steele & White:
2999// https://fmt.dev/papers/p372-steele.pdf.
3000FMT_CONSTEXPR20 inline void format_dragon(basic_fp<uint128_t> value,
3001 unsigned flags, int num_digits,
3002 buffer<char>& buf, int& exp10) {
3003 bigint numerator; // 2 * R in (FPP)^2.
3004 bigint denominator; // 2 * S in (FPP)^2.
3005 // lower and upper are differences between value and corresponding boundaries.
3006 bigint lower; // (M^- in (FPP)^2).
3007 bigint upper_store; // upper's value if different from lower.
3008 bigint* upper = nullptr; // (M^+ in (FPP)^2).
3009 // Shift numerator and denominator by an extra bit or two (if lower boundary
3010 // is closer) to make lower and upper integers. This eliminates multiplication
3011 // by 2 during later computations.
3012 bool is_predecessor_closer = (flags & dragon::predecessor_closer) != 0;
3013 int shift = is_predecessor_closer ? 2 : 1;
3014 if (value.e >= 0) {
3015 numerator = value.f;
3016 numerator <<= value.e + shift;
3017 lower = 1;
3018 lower <<= value.e;
3019 if (is_predecessor_closer) {
3020 upper_store = 1;
3021 upper_store <<= value.e + 1;
3022 upper = &upper_store;
3023 }
3024 denominator.assign_pow10(exp10);
3025 denominator <<= shift;
3026 } else if (exp10 < 0) {
3027 numerator.assign_pow10(-exp10);
3028 lower.assign(numerator);
3029 if (is_predecessor_closer) {
3030 upper_store.assign(numerator);
3031 upper_store <<= 1;
3032 upper = &upper_store;
3033 }
3034 numerator *= value.f;
3035 numerator <<= shift;
3036 denominator = 1;
3037 denominator <<= shift - value.e;
3038 } else {
3039 numerator = value.f;
3040 numerator <<= shift;
3041 denominator.assign_pow10(exp10);
3042 denominator <<= shift - value.e;
3043 lower = 1;
3044 if (is_predecessor_closer) {
3045 upper_store = 1ULL << 1;
3046 upper = &upper_store;
3047 }
3048 }
3049 int even = static_cast<int>((value.f & 1) == 0);
3050 if (!upper) upper = &lower;
3051 bool shortest = num_digits < 0;
3052 if ((flags & dragon::fixup) != 0) {
3053 if (add_compare(numerator, *upper, denominator) + even <= 0) {
3054 --exp10;
3055 numerator *= 10;
3056 if (num_digits < 0) {
3057 lower *= 10;
3058 if (upper != &lower) *upper *= 10;
3059 }
3060 }
3061 if ((flags & dragon::fixed) != 0) adjust_precision(num_digits, exp10 + 1);
3062 }
3063 // Invariant: value == (numerator / denominator) * pow(10, exp10).
3064 if (shortest) {
3065 // Generate the shortest representation.
3066 num_digits = 0;
3067 char* data = buf.data();
3068 for (;;) {
3069 int digit = numerator.divmod_assign(denominator);
3070 bool low = compare(numerator, lower) - even < 0; // numerator <[=] lower.
3071 // numerator + upper >[=] pow10:
3072 bool high = add_compare(numerator, *upper, denominator) + even > 0;
3073 data[num_digits++] = static_cast<char>('0' + digit);
3074 if (low || high) {
3075 if (!low) {
3076 ++data[num_digits - 1];
3077 } else if (high) {
3078 int result = add_compare(numerator, numerator, denominator);
3079 // Round half to even.
3080 if (result > 0 || (result == 0 && (digit % 2) != 0))
3081 ++data[num_digits - 1];
3082 }
3083 buf.try_resize(to_unsigned(num_digits));
3084 exp10 -= num_digits - 1;
3085 return;
3086 }
3087 numerator *= 10;
3088 lower *= 10;
3089 if (upper != &lower) *upper *= 10;
3090 }
3091 }
3092 // Generate the given number of digits.
3093 exp10 -= num_digits - 1;
3094 if (num_digits <= 0) {
3095 auto digit = '0';
3096 if (num_digits == 0) {
3097 denominator *= 10;
3098 digit = add_compare(numerator, numerator, denominator) > 0 ? '1' : '0';
3099 }
3100 buf.push_back(digit);
3101 return;
3102 }
3103 buf.try_resize(to_unsigned(num_digits));
3104 for (int i = 0; i < num_digits - 1; ++i) {
3105 int digit = numerator.divmod_assign(denominator);
3106 buf[i] = static_cast<char>('0' + digit);
3107 numerator *= 10;
3108 }
3109 int digit = numerator.divmod_assign(denominator);
3110 auto result = add_compare(numerator, numerator, denominator);
3111 if (result > 0 || (result == 0 && (digit % 2) != 0)) {
3112 if (digit == 9) {
3113 const auto overflow = '0' + 10;
3114 buf[num_digits - 1] = overflow;
3115 // Propagate the carry.
3116 for (int i = num_digits - 1; i > 0 && buf[i] == overflow; --i) {
3117 buf[i] = '0';
3118 ++buf[i - 1];
3119 }
3120 if (buf[0] == overflow) {
3121 buf[0] = '1';
3122 if ((flags & dragon::fixed) != 0)
3123 buf.push_back('0');
3124 else
3125 ++exp10;
3126 }
3127 return;
3128 }
3129 ++digit;
3130 }
3131 buf[num_digits - 1] = static_cast<char>('0' + digit);
3132}

3134// Formats a floating-point number using the hexfloat format.
3135template <typename Float, FMT_ENABLE_IF(!is_double_double<Float>::value)>
3136FMT_CONSTEXPR20 void format_hexfloat(Float value, format_specs specs,
3137 buffer<char>& buf) {
3138 // float is passed as double to reduce the number of instantiations and to
3139 // simplify implementation.
3140 static_assert(!std::is_same<Float, float>::value, "");
3141
3142 using info = dragonbox::float_info<Float>;
3143
3144 // Assume Float is in the format [sign][exponent][significand].
3145 using carrier_uint = typename info::carrier_uint;
3146
3147 constexpr auto num_float_significand_bits =
3148 detail::num_significand_bits<Float>();
3149
3150 basic_fp<carrier_uint> f(value);
3151 f.e += num_float_significand_bits;
3152 if (!has_implicit_bit<Float>()) --f.e;
3153
3154 constexpr auto num_fraction_bits =
3155 num_float_significand_bits + (has_implicit_bit<Float>() ? 1 : 0);
3156 constexpr auto num_xdigits = (num_fraction_bits + 3) / 4;
3157
3158 constexpr auto leading_shift = ((num_xdigits - 1) * 4);
3159 const auto leading_mask = carrier_uint(0xF) << leading_shift;
3160 const auto leading_xdigit =
3161 static_cast<uint32_t>((f.f & leading_mask) >> leading_shift);
3162 if (leading_xdigit > 1) f.e -= (32 - countl_zero(leading_xdigit) - 1);
3163
3164 int print_xdigits = num_xdigits - 1;
3165 if (specs.precision >= 0 && print_xdigits > specs.precision) {
3166 const int shift = ((print_xdigits - specs.precision - 1) * 4);
3167 const auto mask = carrier_uint(0xF) << shift;
3168 const auto v = static_cast<uint32_t>((f.f & mask) >> shift);
3169
3170 if (v >= 8) {
3171 const auto inc = carrier_uint(1) << (shift + 4);
3172 f.f += inc;
3173 f.f &= ~(inc - 1);
3174 }
3175
3176 // Check long double overflow
3177 if (!has_implicit_bit<Float>()) {
3178 const auto implicit_bit = carrier_uint(1) << num_float_significand_bits;
3179 if ((f.f & implicit_bit) == implicit_bit) {
3180 f.f >>= 4;
3181 f.e += 4;
3182 }
3183 }
3184
3185 print_xdigits = specs.precision;
3186 }
3187
3188 char xdigits[num_bits<carrier_uint>() / 4];
3189 detail::fill_n(xdigits, sizeof(xdigits), '0');
3190 format_uint<4>(xdigits, f.f, num_xdigits, specs.upper);
3191
3192 // Remove zero tail
3193 while (print_xdigits > 0 && xdigits[print_xdigits] == '0') --print_xdigits;
3194
3195 buf.push_back('0');
3196 buf.push_back(specs.upper ? 'X' : 'x');
3197 buf.push_back(xdigits[0]);
3198 if (specs.alt || print_xdigits > 0 || print_xdigits < specs.precision)
3199 buf.push_back('.');
3200 buf.append(xdigits + 1, xdigits + 1 + print_xdigits);
3201 for (; print_xdigits < specs.precision; ++print_xdigits) buf.push_back('0');
3202
3203 buf.push_back(specs.upper ? 'P' : 'p');
3204
3205 uint32_t abs_e;
3206 if (f.e < 0) {
3207 buf.push_back('-');
3208 abs_e = static_cast<uint32_t>(-f.e);
3209 } else {
3210 buf.push_back('+');
3211 abs_e = static_cast<uint32_t>(f.e);
3212 }
3213 format_decimal<char>(appender(buf), abs_e, detail::count_digits(abs_e));
3214}

3218 buffer<char>& buf) {

3222constexpr auto fractional_part_rounding_thresholds(int index) -> uint32_t {
3223 // For checking rounding thresholds.
3224 // The kth entry is chosen to be the smallest integer such that the
3225 // upper 32-bits of 10^(k+1) times it is strictly bigger than 5 * 10^k.
3226 // It is equal to ceil(2^31 + 2^32/10^(k + 1)).
3227 // These are stored in a string literal because we cannot have static arrays
3228 // in constexpr functions and non-static ones are poorly optimized.
3229 return U"\x9999999a\x828f5c29\x80418938\x80068db9\x8000a7c6\x800010c7"
3230 U"\x800001ae\x8000002b"[index];
3231}

3233template <typename Float>
3234FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto format_float(Float value, int precision, float_specs specs,
3235 buffer<char>& buf) -> int {
3236 // float is passed as double to reduce the number of instantiations.
3237 static_assert(!std::is_same<Float, float>::value, "");
3238 FMT_ASSERT(value >= 0, "value is negative");
3239 auto converted_value = convert_float(value);
3240
3241 const bool fixed = specs.format == float_format::fixed;
3242 if (value <= 0) { // <= instead of == to silence a warning.
3243 if (precision <= 0 || !fixed) {
3244 buf.push_back('0');
3245 return 0;
3246 }
3247 buf.try_resize(to_unsigned(precision));
3248 fill_n(buf.data(), precision, '0');
3249 return -precision;
3250 }
3251
3252 int exp = 0;
3253 bool use_dragon = true;
3254 unsigned dragon_flags = 0;
3255 if (!is_fast_float<Float>() || is_constant_evaluated()) {
3256 const auto inv_log2_10 = 0.3010299956639812; // 1 / log2(10)
3257 using info = dragonbox::float_info<decltype(converted_value)>;
3258 const auto f = basic_fp<typename info::carrier_uint>(converted_value);
3259 // Compute exp, an approximate power of 10, such that
3260 // 10^(exp - 1) <= value < 10^exp or 10^exp <= value < 10^(exp + 1).
3261 // This is based on log10(value) == log2(value) / log2(10) and approximation
3262 // of log2(value) by e + num_fraction_bits idea from double-conversion.
3263 auto e = (f.e + count_digits<1>(f.f) - 1) * inv_log2_10 - 1e-10;
3264 exp = static_cast<int>(e);
3265 if (e > exp) ++exp; // Compute ceil.
3266 dragon_flags = dragon::fixup;
3267 } else if (precision < 0) {
3268 // Use Dragonbox for the shortest format.
3269 if (specs.binary32) {
3270 auto dec = dragonbox::to_decimal(static_cast<float>(value));
3271 write<char>(appender(buf), dec.significand);
3272 return dec.exponent;
3273 }
3274 auto dec = dragonbox::to_decimal(static_cast<double>(value));
3275 write<char>(appender(buf), dec.significand);
3276 return dec.exponent;
3277 } else {
3278 // Extract significand bits and exponent bits.
3279 using info = dragonbox::float_info<double>;
3280 auto br = bit_cast<uint64_t>(static_cast<double>(value));
3281
3282 const uint64_t significand_mask =
3283 (static_cast<uint64_t>(1) << num_significand_bits<double>()) - 1;
3284 uint64_t significand = (br & significand_mask);
3285 int exponent = static_cast<int>((br & exponent_mask<double>()) >>
3286 num_significand_bits<double>());
3287
3288 if (exponent != 0) { // Check if normal.
3289 exponent -= exponent_bias<double>() + num_significand_bits<double>();
3290 significand |=
3291 (static_cast<uint64_t>(1) << num_significand_bits<double>());
3292 significand <<= 1;
3293 } else {
3294 // Normalize subnormal inputs.
3295 FMT_ASSERT(significand != 0, "zeros should not appear here");
3296 int shift = countl_zero(significand);
3297 FMT_ASSERT(shift >= num_bits<uint64_t>() - num_significand_bits<double>(),
3298 "");
3299 shift -= (num_bits<uint64_t>() - num_significand_bits<double>() - 2);
3300 exponent = (std::numeric_limits<double>::min_exponent -
3301 num_significand_bits<double>()) -
3302 shift;
3303 significand <<= shift;
3304 }
3305
3306 // Compute the first several nonzero decimal significand digits.
3307 // We call the number we get the first segment.
3308 const int k = info::kappa - dragonbox::floor_log10_pow2(exponent);
3309 exp = -k;
3310 const int beta = exponent + dragonbox::floor_log2_pow10(k);
3311 uint64_t first_segment;
3312 bool has_more_segments;
3313 int digits_in_the_first_segment;
3314 {
3315 const auto r = dragonbox::umul192_upper128(
3316 significand << beta, dragonbox::get_cached_power(k));
3317 first_segment = r.high();
3318 has_more_segments = r.low() != 0;
3319
3320 // The first segment can have 18 ~ 19 digits.
3321 if (first_segment >= 1000000000000000000ULL) {
3322 digits_in_the_first_segment = 19;
3323 } else {
3324 // When it is of 18-digits, we align it to 19-digits by adding a bogus
3325 // zero at the end.
3326 digits_in_the_first_segment = 18;
3327 first_segment *= 10;
3328 }
3329 }
3330
3331 // Compute the actual number of decimal digits to print.
3332 if (fixed) adjust_precision(precision, exp + digits_in_the_first_segment);
3333
3334 // Use Dragon4 only when there might be not enough digits in the first
3335 // segment.
3336 if (digits_in_the_first_segment > precision) {
3337 use_dragon = false;
3338
3339 if (precision <= 0) {
3340 exp += digits_in_the_first_segment;
3341
3342 if (precision < 0) {
3343 // Nothing to do, since all we have are just leading zeros.
3344 buf.try_resize(0);
3345 } else {
3346 // We may need to round-up.
3347 buf.try_resize(1);
3348 if ((first_segment | static_cast<uint64_t>(has_more_segments)) >
3349 5000000000000000000ULL) {
3350 buf[0] = '1';
3351 } else {
3352 buf[0] = '0';
3353 }
3354 }
3355 } // precision <= 0
3356 else {
3357 exp += digits_in_the_first_segment - precision;
3358
3359 // When precision > 0, we divide the first segment into three
3360 // subsegments, each with 9, 9, and 0 ~ 1 digits so that each fits
3361 // in 32-bits which usually allows faster calculation than in
3362 // 64-bits. Since some compiler (e.g. MSVC) doesn't know how to optimize
3363 // division-by-constant for large 64-bit divisors, we do it here
3364 // manually. The magic number 7922816251426433760 below is equal to
3365 // ceil(2^(64+32) / 10^10).
3366 const uint32_t first_subsegment = static_cast<uint32_t>(
3367 dragonbox::umul128_upper64(first_segment, 7922816251426433760ULL) >>
3368 32);
3369 const uint64_t second_third_subsegments =
3370 first_segment - first_subsegment * 10000000000ULL;
3371
3372 uint64_t prod;
3373 uint32_t digits;
3374 bool should_round_up;
3375 int number_of_digits_to_print = precision > 9 ? 9 : precision;
3376
3377 // Print a 9-digits subsegment, either the first or the second.
3378 auto print_subsegment = [&](uint32_t subsegment, char* buffer) {
3379 int number_of_digits_printed = 0;
3380
3381 // If we want to print an odd number of digits from the subsegment,
3382 if ((number_of_digits_to_print & 1) != 0) {
3383 // Convert to 64-bit fixed-point fractional form with 1-digit
3384 // integer part. The magic number 720575941 is a good enough
3385 // approximation of 2^(32 + 24) / 10^8; see
3386 // https://jk-jeon.github.io/posts/2022/12/fixed-precision-formatting/#fixed-length-case
3387 // for details.
3388 prod = ((subsegment * static_cast<uint64_t>(720575941)) >> 24) + 1;
3389 digits = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod >> 32);
3390 *buffer = static_cast<char>('0' + digits);
3391 number_of_digits_printed++;
3392 }
3393 // If we want to print an even number of digits from the
3394 // first_subsegment,
3395 else {
3396 // Convert to 64-bit fixed-point fractional form with 2-digits
3397 // integer part. The magic number 450359963 is a good enough
3398 // approximation of 2^(32 + 20) / 10^7; see
3399 // https://jk-jeon.github.io/posts/2022/12/fixed-precision-formatting/#fixed-length-case
3400 // for details.
3401 prod = ((subsegment * static_cast<uint64_t>(450359963)) >> 20) + 1;
3402 digits = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod >> 32);
3403 copy2(buffer, digits2(digits));
3404 number_of_digits_printed += 2;
3405 }
3406
3407 // Print all digit pairs.
3408 while (number_of_digits_printed < number_of_digits_to_print) {
3409 prod = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod) * static_cast<uint64_t>(100);
3410 digits = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod >> 32);
3411 copy2(buffer + number_of_digits_printed, digits2(digits));
3412 number_of_digits_printed += 2;
3413 }
3414 };
3415
3416 // Print first subsegment.
3417 print_subsegment(first_subsegment, buf.data());
3418
3419 // Perform rounding if the first subsegment is the last subsegment to
3420 // print.
3421 if (precision <= 9) {
3422 // Rounding inside the subsegment.
3423 // We round-up if:
3424 // - either the fractional part is strictly larger than 1/2, or
3425 // - the fractional part is exactly 1/2 and the last digit is odd.
3426 // We rely on the following observations:
3427 // - If fractional_part >= threshold, then the fractional part is
3428 // strictly larger than 1/2.
3429 // - If the MSB of fractional_part is set, then the fractional part
3430 // must be at least 1/2.
3431 // - When the MSB of fractional_part is set, either
3432 // second_third_subsegments being nonzero or has_more_segments
3433 // being true means there are further digits not printed, so the
3434 // fractional part is strictly larger than 1/2.
3435 if (precision < 9) {
3436 uint32_t fractional_part = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod);
3437 should_round_up =
3438 fractional_part >= fractional_part_rounding_thresholds(
3439 8 - number_of_digits_to_print) ||
3440 ((fractional_part >> 31) &
3441 ((digits & 1) | (second_third_subsegments != 0) |
3442 has_more_segments)) != 0;
3443 }
3444 // Rounding at the subsegment boundary.
3445 // In this case, the fractional part is at least 1/2 if and only if
3446 // second_third_subsegments >= 5000000000ULL, and is strictly larger
3447 // than 1/2 if we further have either second_third_subsegments >
3448 // 5000000000ULL or has_more_segments == true.
3449 else {
3450 should_round_up = second_third_subsegments > 5000000000ULL ||
3451 (second_third_subsegments == 5000000000ULL &&
3452 ((digits & 1) != 0 || has_more_segments));
3453 }
3454 }
3455 // Otherwise, print the second subsegment.
3456 else {
3457 // Compilers are not aware of how to leverage the maximum value of
3458 // second_third_subsegments to find out a better magic number which
3459 // allows us to eliminate an additional shift. 1844674407370955162 =
3460 // ceil(2^64/10) < ceil(2^64*(10^9/(10^10 - 1))).
3461 const uint32_t second_subsegment =
3462 static_cast<uint32_t>(dragonbox::umul128_upper64(
3463 second_third_subsegments, 1844674407370955162ULL));
3464 const uint32_t third_subsegment =
3465 static_cast<uint32_t>(second_third_subsegments) -
3466 second_subsegment * 10;
3467
3468 number_of_digits_to_print = precision - 9;
3469 print_subsegment(second_subsegment, buf.data() + 9);
3470
3471 // Rounding inside the subsegment.
3472 if (precision < 18) {
3473 // The condition third_subsegment != 0 implies that the segment was
3474 // of 19 digits, so in this case the third segment should be
3475 // consisting of a genuine digit from the input.
3476 uint32_t fractional_part = static_cast<uint32_t>(prod);
3477 should_round_up =
3478 fractional_part >= fractional_part_rounding_thresholds(
3479 8 - number_of_digits_to_print) ||
3480 ((fractional_part >> 31) &
3481 ((digits & 1) | (third_subsegment != 0) |
3482 has_more_segments)) != 0;
3483 }
3484 // Rounding at the subsegment boundary.
3485 else {
3486 // In this case, the segment must be of 19 digits, thus
3487 // the third subsegment should be consisting of a genuine digit from
3488 // the input.
3489 should_round_up = third_subsegment > 5 ||
3490 (third_subsegment == 5 &&
3491 ((digits & 1) != 0 || has_more_segments));
3492 }
3493 }
3494
3495 // Round-up if necessary.
3496 if (should_round_up) {
3497 ++buf[precision - 1];
3498 for (int i = precision - 1; i > 0 && buf[i] > '9'; --i) {
3499 buf[i] = '0';
3500 ++buf[i - 1];
3501 }
3502 if (buf[0] > '9') {
3503 buf[0] = '1';
3504 if (fixed)
3505 buf[precision++] = '0';
3506 else
3507 ++exp;
3508 }
3509 }
3510 buf.try_resize(to_unsigned(precision));
3511 }
3512 } // if (digits_in_the_first_segment > precision)
3513 else {
3514 // Adjust the exponent for its use in Dragon4.
3515 exp += digits_in_the_first_segment - 1;
3516 }
3517 }
3518 if (use_dragon) {
3519 auto f = basic_fp<uint128_t>();
3520 bool is_predecessor_closer = specs.binary32
3521 ? f.assign(static_cast<float>(value))
3522 : f.assign(converted_value);
3523 if (is_predecessor_closer) dragon_flags |= dragon::predecessor_closer;
3524 if (fixed) dragon_flags |= dragon::fixed;
3525 // Limit precision to the maximum possible number of significant digits in
3526 // an IEEE754 double because we don't need to generate zeros.
3527 const int max_double_digits = 767;
3528 if (precision > max_double_digits) precision = max_double_digits;
3529 format_dragon(f, dragon_flags, precision, buf, exp);
3530 }
3531 if (!fixed && !specs.showpoint) {
3532 // Remove trailing zeros.
3533 auto num_digits = buf.size();
3534 while (num_digits > 0 && buf[num_digits - 1] == '0') {
3535 --num_digits;
3536 ++exp;
3537 }
3538 buf.try_resize(num_digits);
3539 }
3540 return exp;
3541}
3542
3543template <typename Char, typename OutputIt, typename T>
3544FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto write_float(OutputIt out, T value, format_specs specs,
3545 locale_ref loc) -> OutputIt {
3546 sign_t sign = specs.sign;
3547 if (detail::signbit(value)) { // value < 0 is false for NaN so use signbit.
3548 sign = sign::minus;
3549 value = -value;
3550 } else if (sign == sign::minus) {
3551 sign = sign::none;
3552 }
3553
3554 if (!detail::isfinite(value))
3555 return write_nonfinite<Char>(out, detail::isnan(value), specs, sign);
3556
3557 if (specs.align == align::numeric && sign) {
3558 auto it = reserve(out, 1);
3559 *it++ = detail::sign<Char>(sign);
3560 out = base_iterator(out, it);
3561 sign = sign::none;
3562 if (specs.width != 0) --specs.width;
3563 }
3564
3565 memory_buffer buffer;
3566 if (specs.type == presentation_type::hexfloat) {
3567 if (sign) buffer.push_back(detail::sign<char>(sign));
3568 format_hexfloat(convert_float(value), specs, buffer);
3569 return write_bytes<Char, align::right>(out, {buffer.data(), buffer.size()},
3570 specs);
3571 }
3572
3573 int precision = specs.precision >= 0 || specs.type == presentation_type::none
3574 ? specs.precision
3575 : 6;
3576 if (specs.type == presentation_type::exp) {
3577 if (precision == max_value<int>())
3578 report_error("number is too big");
3579 else
3580 ++precision;
3581 } else if (specs.type != presentation_type::fixed && precision == 0) {
3582 precision = 1;
3583 }
3584 float_specs fspecs = parse_float_type_spec(specs);
3585 fspecs.sign = sign;
3586 if (const_check(std::is_same<T, float>())) fspecs.binary32 = true;
3587 int exp = format_float(convert_float(value), precision, fspecs, buffer);
3588 fspecs.precision = precision;
3589 auto f = big_decimal_fp{buffer.data(), static_cast<int>(buffer.size()), exp};
3590 return write_float<Char>(out, f, specs, fspecs, loc);
3591}

3593template <typename Char, typename OutputIt, typename T,
3594 FMT_ENABLE_IF(is_floating_point<T>::value)>
3595FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto write(OutputIt out, T value, format_specs specs,
3596 locale_ref loc = {}) -> OutputIt {
3597 if (const_check(!is_supported_floating_point(value))) return out;
3598 return specs.localized && write_loc(out, value, specs, loc)
3599 ? out
3600 : write_float<Char>(out, value, specs, loc);
3601}

3603template <typename Char, typename OutputIt, typename T,
3604 FMT_ENABLE_IF(is_fast_float<T>::value)>
3605FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto write(OutputIt out, T value) -> OutputIt {
3606 if (is_constant_evaluated()) return write<Char>(out, value, format_specs());
3607 if (const_check(!is_supported_floating_point(value))) return out;
3608
3609 auto sign = sign_t::none;
3610 if (detail::signbit(value)) {
3611 sign = sign::minus;
3612 value = -value;
3613 }
3614
3615 constexpr auto specs = format_specs();
3616 using floaty = conditional_t<std::is_same<T, long double>::value, double, T>;
3617 using floaty_uint = typename dragonbox::float_info<floaty>::carrier_uint;
3618 floaty_uint mask = exponent_mask<floaty>();
3619 if ((bit_cast<floaty_uint>(value) & mask) == mask)
3620 return write_nonfinite<Char>(out, std::isnan(value), specs, sign);
3621
3622 auto fspecs = float_specs();
3623 fspecs.sign = sign;
3624 auto dec = dragonbox::to_decimal(static_cast<floaty>(value));
3625 return write_float<Char>(out, dec, specs, fspecs, {});
3626}

3887 * **Example**:

3905 * language runtime, for example a file opening error, and writes it to `out`.
3906 * The format is the same as the one used by `std::system_error(ec, message)`

3923/// A fast integer formatter.
3924class format_int {
3925 private:
3926 // Buffer should be large enough to hold all digits (digits10 + 1),
3927 // a sign and a null character.
3928 enum { buffer_size = std::numeric_limits<unsigned long long>::digits10 + 3 };
3929 mutable char buffer_[buffer_size];
3930 char* str_;
3931
3932 template <typename UInt>
3933 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto format_unsigned(UInt value) -> char* {
3934 auto n = static_cast<detail::uint32_or_64_or_128_t<UInt>>(value);
3935 return detail::format_decimal(buffer_, n, buffer_size - 1).begin;
3936 }
3937
3938 template <typename Int>
3939 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto format_signed(Int value) -> char* {
3940 auto abs_value = static_cast<detail::uint32_or_64_or_128_t<Int>>(value);
3941 bool negative = value < 0;
3942 if (negative) abs_value = 0 - abs_value;
3943 auto begin = format_unsigned(abs_value);
3944 if (negative) *--begin = '-';
3945 return begin;
3946 }
3947
3948 public:
3949 explicit FMT_CONSTEXPR20 format_int(int value) : str_(format_signed(value)) {}
3950 explicit FMT_CONSTEXPR20 format_int(long value)
3951 : str_(format_signed(value)) {}
3952 explicit FMT_CONSTEXPR20 format_int(long long value)
3953 : str_(format_signed(value)) {}
3954 explicit FMT_CONSTEXPR20 format_int(unsigned value)
3955 : str_(format_unsigned(value)) {}
3956 explicit FMT_CONSTEXPR20 format_int(unsigned long value)
3957 : str_(format_unsigned(value)) {}
3958 explicit FMT_CONSTEXPR20 format_int(unsigned long long value)
3959 : str_(format_unsigned(value)) {}
3960
3961 /// Returns the number of characters written to the output buffer.
3962 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto size() const -> size_t {
3963 return detail::to_unsigned(buffer_ - str_ + buffer_size - 1);
3964 }
3965
3966 /// Returns a pointer to the output buffer content. No terminating null
3967 /// character is appended.
3968 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto data() const -> const char* { return str_; }
3969
3970 /// Returns a pointer to the output buffer content with terminating null
3971 /// character appended.
3972 FMT_CONSTEXPR20 auto c_str() const -> const char* {
3973 buffer_[buffer_size - 1] = '\0';
3974 return str_;
3975 }
3976
3977 /// Returns the content of the output buffer as an `std::string`.
3978 auto str() const -> std::string { return std::string(str_, size()); }
3979};

4021 * **Example**:

4032 *
4033 * **Example**:

4040 return static_cast<underlying_t<Enum>>(e);

4088 * locale-independent thousands separator.

4143template <typename T, typename Char = char> struct nested_formatter {
4144 private:
4145 int width_;
4146 detail::fill_t fill_;
4147 align_t align_ : 4;
4148 formatter<T, Char> formatter_;
4149
4150 public:
4151 constexpr nested_formatter() : width_(0), align_(align_t::none) {}
4152
4153 FMT_CONSTEXPR auto parse(basic_format_parse_context<Char>& ctx)
4154 -> decltype(ctx.begin()) {
4155 auto specs = detail::dynamic_format_specs<Char>();
4156 auto it = parse_format_specs(ctx.begin(), ctx.end(), specs, ctx,
4157 detail::type::none_type);
4158 width_ = specs.width;
4159 fill_ = specs.fill;
4160 align_ = specs.align;
4161 ctx.advance_to(it);
4162 return formatter_.parse(ctx);
4163 }
4164
4165 template <typename FormatContext, typename F>
4166 auto write_padded(FormatContext& ctx, F write) const -> decltype(ctx.out()) {
4167 if (width_ == 0) return write(ctx.out());
4168 auto buf = basic_memory_buffer<Char>();
4169 write(basic_appender<Char>(buf));
4170 auto specs = format_specs();
4171 specs.width = width_;
4172 specs.fill = fill_;
4173 specs.align = align_;
4174 return detail::write<Char>(
4175 ctx.out(), basic_string_view<Char>(buf.data(), buf.size()), specs);
4176 }
4177
4178 auto nested(const T& value) const -> nested_view<T, Char> {
4179 return nested_view<T, Char>{&formatter_, &value};
4180 }
4181};

4183/**
4184 * Converts `value` to `std::string` using the default format for type `T`.
4185 *
4186 * **Example**:
4187 *
4188 * std::string answer = fmt::to_string(42);
4189 */
4190template <typename T, FMT_ENABLE_IF(!std::is_integral<T>::value &&
4191 !detail::has_format_as<T>::value)>
4192inline auto to_string(const T& value) -> std::string {
4193 auto buffer = memory_buffer();
4194 detail::write<char>(appender(buffer), value);
4195 return {buffer.data(), buffer.size()};
4196}
4197
4198template <typename T, FMT_ENABLE_IF(std::is_integral<T>::value)>
4199FMT_NODISCARD inline auto to_string(T value) -> std::string {
4200 // The buffer should be large enough to store the number including the sign
4201 // or "false" for bool.
4202 constexpr int max_size = detail::digits10<T>() + 2;
4203 char buffer[max_size > 5 ? static_cast<unsigned>(max_size) : 5];
4204 char* begin = buffer;
4205 return std::string(begin, detail::write<char>(begin, value));
4206}
4207
4208template <typename Char, size_t SIZE>
4209FMT_NODISCARD auto to_string(const basic_memory_buffer<Char, SIZE>& buf)
4210 -> std::basic_string<Char> {
4211 auto size = buf.size();
4212 detail::assume(size < std::basic_string<Char>().max_size());
4213 return std::basic_string<Char>(buf.data(), size);
4214}
4215
4216template <typename T, FMT_ENABLE_IF(!std::is_integral<T>::value &&
4217 detail::has_format_as<T>::value)>
4218inline auto to_string(const T& value) -> std::string {
4219 return to_string(format_as(value));
4220}

4226template <typename Char>
4227void vformat_to(buffer<Char>& buf, basic_string_view<Char> fmt,
4228 typename vformat_args<Char>::type args, locale_ref loc) {
4229 auto out = basic_appender<Char>(buf);
4230 if (fmt.size() == 2 && equal2(fmt.data(), "{}")) {
4231 auto arg = args.get(0);
4232 if (!arg) report_error("argument not found");
4233 arg.visit(default_arg_formatter<Char>{out, args, loc});
4234 return;
4235 }
4236
4237 struct format_handler {
4238 basic_format_parse_context<Char> parse_context;
4239 buffered_context<Char> context;
4240
4241 format_handler(basic_appender<Char> p_out, basic_string_view<Char> str,
4242 basic_format_args<buffered_context<Char>> p_args,
4243 locale_ref p_loc)
4244 : parse_context(str), context(p_out, p_args, p_loc) {}
4245
4246 void on_text(const Char* begin, const Char* end) {
4247 auto text = basic_string_view<Char>(begin, to_unsigned(end - begin));
4248 context.advance_to(write<Char>(context.out(), text));
4249 }
4250
4251 FMT_CONSTEXPR auto on_arg_id() -> int {
4252 return parse_context.next_arg_id();
4253 }
4254 FMT_CONSTEXPR auto on_arg_id(int id) -> int {
4255 parse_context.check_arg_id(id);
4256 return id;
4257 }
4258 FMT_CONSTEXPR auto on_arg_id(basic_string_view<Char> id) -> int {
4259 parse_context.check_arg_id(id);
4260 int arg_id = context.arg_id(id);
4261 if (arg_id < 0) report_error("argument not found");
4262 return arg_id;
4263 }
4264
4265 FMT_INLINE void on_replacement_field(int id, const Char*) {
4266 auto arg = get_arg(context, id);
4267 context.advance_to(arg.visit(default_arg_formatter<Char>{
4268 context.out(), context.args(), context.locale()}));
4269 }
4270
4271 auto on_format_specs(int id, const Char* begin, const Char* end)
4272 -> const Char* {
4273 auto arg = get_arg(context, id);
4274 // Not using a visitor for custom types gives better codegen.
4275 if (arg.format_custom(begin, parse_context, context))
4276 return parse_context.begin();
4277 auto specs = detail::dynamic_format_specs<Char>();
4278 begin = parse_format_specs(begin, end, specs, parse_context, arg.type());
4279 detail::handle_dynamic_spec<detail::width_checker>(
4280 specs.width, specs.width_ref, context);
4281 detail::handle_dynamic_spec<detail::precision_checker>(
4282 specs.precision, specs.precision_ref, context);
4283 if (begin == end || *begin != '}')
4284 report_error("missing '}' in format string");
4285 context.advance_to(arg.visit(
4286 arg_formatter<Char>{context.out(), specs, context.locale()}));
4287 return begin;
4288 }
4289
4290 FMT_NORETURN void on_error(const char* message) { report_error(message); }
4291 };
4292 detail::parse_format_string<false>(fmt, format_handler(out, fmt, args, loc));
4293}

4311template <typename T, typename Char, type TYPE>
4312template <typename FormatContext>
4313FMT_CONSTEXPR FMT_INLINE auto native_formatter<T, Char, TYPE>::format(
4314 const T& val, FormatContext& ctx) const -> decltype(ctx.out()) {
4315 if (specs_.width_ref.kind == arg_id_kind::none &&
4316 specs_.precision_ref.kind == arg_id_kind::none) {
4317 return write<Char>(ctx.out(), val, specs_, ctx.locale());
4318 }
4319 auto specs = specs_;
4320 handle_dynamic_spec<width_checker>(specs.width, specs.width_ref, ctx);
4321 handle_dynamic_spec<precision_checker>(specs.precision, specs.precision_ref,
4322 ctx);
4323 return write<Char>(ctx.out(), val, specs, ctx.locale());
4324}
